{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"6868a40e-d0f9-405f-967f-3247510aee2c","content":"Here are the most common options depending on your stack:\n\n**ASP.NET Core**\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi --auth Individual   # Identity-based auth\ndotnet new webapi --auth SingleOrg    # Azure AD (single tenant)\ndotnet new webapi --auth MultiOrg     # Azure AD (multi-tenant)\ndotnet new webapi --auth Windows      # Windows auth\n```\n\n**Node.js** — Use Express/Fastify with Passport.js, or a framework like NestJS with built-in guards for JWT, OAuth2, etc.\n\n**Python** — Django REST Framework (session/token auth) or FastAPI (OAuth2/JWT via `python-jose`).\n\n**Key auth strategies across stacks:**\n- **JWT Bearer tokens** — stateless, most common for APIs\n- **OAuth 2.0 / OpenID Connect** — delegated auth (Google, GitHub, etc.)\n- **API keys** — simple, good for service-to-service\n- **Cookie/session** — traditional, better for browser clients\n\nWant me to scaffold a specific project? Let me know your preferred language/framework.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"8b5f2dc4-c9ea-4995-bb91-d91db5d4920e","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking a general knowledge question about web API project templates and authentication options. This doesn't require any tool calls - I can answer from my knowledge of common web frameworks.\n\nLet me provide a concise answer covering the most common frameworks.","outputTokens":322,"requestId":"4802:B0AF0:100785:132DE7:69EABDED"},"id":"c0363654-c4d7-4593-a42a-ecd413333c12","timestamp":"2026-04-24T00:48:55.682Z","parentId":"d449e736-372e-4a7b-a635-294457c53d95"}
